"title": "5321: furnace",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5321: furnace",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A closed fireplace made of brick or stone for domestic or industrial usage. Used figuratively, it represents God's presence, testing and judgment.</p>\n<h2>Everyday use of furnaces</h2>\n<h3>As a stove or oven</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh3:11\">NEH 3:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:38\">NEH 12:38</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam5:10\">LAM 5:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:6\">DAN 3:6</a></p>\n<h3>As a kiln</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod9:8\">EXO 9:8</a></p>\n<h3>For smelting metals</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps12:6\">PSA 12:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:21\">PRO 27:21</a></p>\n<h2>Figurative use of furnaces</h2>\n<h3>As a symbol of God's majestic presence</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:17\">GEN 15:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:9\">ISA 31:9</a></p>\n<h3>As a symbol of affliction and testing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:10\">ISA 48:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:20\">DEU 4:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:51\">1KI 8:51</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:3\">PRO 17:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:4\">JER 11:4</a></p>\n<h3>As a symbol of God's wrath</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:42\">MAT 13:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:28\">GEN 19:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps21:9\">PSA 21:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:17-Ezek22:22\">EZK 22:17–22:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal4:1\">MAL 4:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:50\">MAT 13:50</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:2\">REV 9:2</a></p>",
